To help address this issue, you can add comments to your code to indicate that a private member variable should only be accessed through a getter method, regardless of whether it's within the class or outside it. This makes it clear that the variable is intended to be used in a specific way and helps prevent accidental misuse of it.

Here's an example of how you can use comments to provide instructions for using private member variables:

```
class MyClass {
  String _myField = 'initial value';

  String get myField => _myField;

  // Only access _myField through the myField getter method
